=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Part of the explanation is tha=
t this year=E2=80=99s holiday holdovers aren=E2=80=99t as big as a <em>Star=
 Wars </em>or an <em>Avatar</em>, but there=E2=80=99s also a conspicuous ab=
sence of an Oscar contender with broad appeal. The earnings from those main=
stream winners are the difference between pre- and post-Covid box office, w=
hen big movies=E2=80=94ones that didn=E2=80=99t need awards attention to su=
cceed=E2=80=94pulled down a handful of nominations to push them over the to=
p and boost total gross
during the first months of the year.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Indeed, this weeke=
nd=E2=80=99s box office is down 46 percent from the same period in 2020, wh=
ich was also the last time one of those bigger movies got an awards season =
boost: <strong>Sam Mendes</strong>=E2=80=99 World War I thriller <em>1917</=
em> raced to $159 million in North America and $384 million worldwide on a =
$95 million budget. That year=E2=80=99s eventual best picture winner,
<em>Parasite</em>, earned $53 million in North America, a near-record domes=
tic amount for a non-English-language feature, and $262 million worldwide. =
Just one year earlier, best picture winner <em>Green Book </em>earned more =
than $320 million worldwide, including $71 million in China.=C2=A0</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-b=
ottom:0px;">The closest thing we=E2=80=99ve had to a mainstream Oscar seaso=
n breakout hit since the beginning of the Covid
pandemic was <strong>Yorgos Lanthimos</strong>=E2=80=99s <em>Poor Things</e=
m>, which earned $111 million worldwide in late 2023 and early 2024 and won=
 <strong>Emma Stone </strong>her second Oscar for best actress. This season=
, judging by the first post-noms weekend, the only two Oscar bump beneficia=
ries are Searchlight=E2=80=99s <em>A Complete Unknown, </em>the <strong>Bob=
 Dylan</strong> biopic starring <strong>Timoth=C3=A9e Chalamet</strong>, an=
d A24=E2=80=99s epic <em>The Brutalist, </em>starring <strong>Adrien
Brody</strong>. <em>A Complete Unknown </em>lost 490 theaters after playing=
